<h5><strong>&nbsp;jQuery Event methods </strong></h5>
<p>

    The <code>mousedown()</code> method attaches an event handler function to element.
    <br><br>
    The function is executed, when the left, middle or right mouse button is pressed down, while the mouse is over the element.
    <br><br>
    Examples : <br><br>
    <code>$("p").mousedown(function(){</code><br>
    <code>&nbsp;&nbsp;// handle the event</code><br>
    <code>});</code><br>
    When any mouse button is pressed in the paragraph area, this function will be executed.
    <br><br>

